Yay for the onion haters! That leaves more for me!!Now we know why sweetpepper isn't called sweetonion. There's a middle-eastern dish called... mujadara that is rice, lentils and caramelized onions. It is one of my favorite comfort foods. Easy to make, good for you, and full of tasty onion.If you have a spare 8 hours, caramelizing onions in a crock pot is ideal. Toss them in, with a dab of butter or olive oil and a tablespoon or so of water set crock pot to low, cover and walk away. Stir them every hour or so. Perfect onions for french onion soup.
