I was always an onion fiend, I'd put them on metaphorically everything. I still do, but things have taken a disturbing turn. I have no problem with the onion breath but lately onions seems to be causing ... a fire down below for lack of a better term. I feel like my body has betrayed me. Damn 40's.Quick tip: for faster browning of sauteed onions, toss a 1/4-cup or so of water into the pan when you start. It speeds up the onions giving up their own juices so it all can boil off and let the Maillard reaction start.By the way...Hound of Cullen wrote:There's a middle-eastern dish called... mujadara that is rice, lentils and caramelized onions. It is one of my favorite comfort foods. Easy to make, good for you, and full of tasty onion.OMG! I am so making mujaddara this weekend.
